<chapter name="tile.heat_exchange_start.name"/>
<lore>
In your attempts to make the best use out of your combustable fuels, use cool fluids just isn't enough anymore and the need to heat and cool fluids into its various temperatures is required.
</lore>
<chapter name="Information"/>
The Heat Exchanger is used to cool/heat fluids and is made out of 3 parts: Start, middle and end which are assembled together to form a multiblock.
Using upto 3 middle sections to make the process go faster.
